<Page
    x:Class="Bluebird.Pages.HelpPage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
    xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
    NavigationCacheMode="Required"
    mc:Ignorable="d">

    <RichTextBlock Margin="10">
        <Paragraph FontSize="30" FontWeight="Medium">Help</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph FontSize="20">Q: There is a bug with the application! How can I report it?</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>
            You can create an issue on the official <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://github.com/bluebird-developers/browser/issues">GitHub issues page</Hyperlink>
            , which allows us to easily track the issue. You can also contact us on either of these two discord servers</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>
            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://discord.com/invite/AxmR3HGTnJ">Developer Sanctuary</Hyperlink>
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>
            or <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://discord.com/invite/rdcYUZj3ej">Microsoft Edge Hub</Hyperlink>
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>You can chat with us there, suggest features or enhancements, report bugs and get access to the latest information</Paragraph>

        <Paragraph FontSize="20">Q: I cannot view any webpages and I get an error saying I need to a WebView2 runtime, what is it and how can I get that?</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>The WebView2 runtime is the component used to display webpages, without this component installed you cannot view any websites in Bluebird.</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>
            It is preinstalled on Windows 10 and Windows 11, if you uninstalled it and need to install it again, download it <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/">here</Hyperlink>
        </Paragraph>
    </RichTextBlock>
</Page>
